<br>
My old guild had a point system that weighed heavy on merit and NB4G.<br>
<br>
Now as far as pick up groups I am very much a NB4G person but I am also realistic.  There are many places where certain classes aint gettin much.<br>
<br>
It is also a case of trust.  I try to group with people I can trust or know when we go item hunting or what have ya.<br>
<br>
Other than that its main loot and split after.<br>
<br>
My classic example of the exception is the King camp in OS.  How many casters are you going to get if you dont roll for the items that drop there.  I was in that camp on the old server and a bracer dropped two of the times i was there.  I lost both rolls....killed me as an ogre warrior to loose but I didnt fuss.  One guy was a warrior....didnt need shrink but hey its a cool bracer.  The other Im sure sold it for 50k or traded it for a lodi shield or whatever....was fair.  He put the time in, did the camp.  He didnt offer it to me but I wouldnt have bought it either.  I wanted to loot my own.  I did eventually get one and the wife even got a fungi tunic on a roll.<br>
<br>
It really depends on the situation.<br>
<br>
As everyone who has ever posted on this subject has said the most important thing to do is to establish it from the get go how it is handled and ALWAYS be fair.  The orc pick you fight over today could cost you the King group you wanted to get into and cant because you were unfair on loot way back when you were level 5.<br>
<br>
Hope it helps.<br>
<br>
