<br>
I am also a huge proponent of NBG but realize that at times you just have to grin, bear it, and let everyone roll.<br>
<br>
Different servers have different thresholds for this. On regular servers, unfortunately, greed outweighs need more often due to the value of items on the player market. Like Xelena, I came here from Test where there is no economy to speak of and need usually trumps greed. FV seems to me to be somewhere in the middle...hopefully closer to the Test way.<br>
<br>
The most important thing is that policy be agreed to by all BEFORE the goodies drop.<br>
<br>
At low levels where coin loot is more of an issue, /autosplit is problematic. It doesn't make change. If a mob drops 4pp 10gp 20sp 40cp, in a group of six, the looter gets 4pp 5gp 5sp 10cp and everyone else gets 0pp 1gp 3sp 6cp. Not much of a split, is it? If you get into a group where one person pounces on every corpse, justifying it with &quot;but I have split turned on&quot;, reach for the Disband button.<br>
<br>
-- Mystikat, Dar Khura with zero tolerance for hogs<br>
